00:13:00.450 --> 00:13:06.176
So we stop asking, show me the rule, which is that lawyer mindset, and we start asking, will this build us up?

00:13:06.437 --> 00:13:08.439
We move from a courtroom to a family room.

00:13:08.579 --> 00:13:09.861
We aren't trying to win a case.

00:13:10.301 --> 00:13:11.763
We are trying to care for our siblings.

00:13:11.983 --> 00:13:12.784
So let's get practical.

00:13:12.844 --> 00:13:13.725
We've done the theology.

00:13:13.745 --> 00:13:14.626
We've felt the weight of it.

00:13:15.006 --> 00:13:20.432
If I'm walking into my small group or a church potluck at CCCC this week, how do I actually do this?

00:13:20.593 --> 00:13:21.874
The source gave us three habits.

00:13:22.174 --> 00:13:24.537
Yes, and I love these because they are so actionable.

00:13:24.817 --> 00:13:27.480
The first one, ask Ask Engaging Act.

00:13:27.961 --> 00:13:29.042
That seems simple enough.

00:13:29.154 --> 00:13:30.856
It is, but we rarely do it.

00:13:31.397 --> 00:13:36.723
If you're in mixed company, maybe you're hosting, just ask, hey, is everyone comfortable if we serve wine with dinner?

00:13:37.104 --> 00:13:39.006
Does anyone have an issue with this type of music?

00:13:39.286 --> 00:13:42.310
It signals immediately that you care more about them than the stuff.

00:13:42.611 --> 00:13:44.813
Right, it removes the surprise factor.

00:13:45.314 --> 00:13:48.278
It lowers the anxiety in the room before it even starts.

00:13:49.038 --> 00:13:53.063
Okay, habit number two, teach without pushing.

00:13:53.704 --> 00:13:58.450
This is specifically for the strong believer who is frustrated with the weak believer.

00:13:58.562 --> 00:14:01.626
You see someone who is trapped in legalism.

00:14:02.227 --> 00:14:06.312
Maybe they think they can't watch certain movies or play cards, and you just want to fix them.

00:14:06.493 --> 00:14:08.075
You want to shake them and say, you're missing out.

00:14:08.115 --> 00:14:09.196
The Bible doesn't say that.

00:14:09.316 --> 00:14:11.299
But you can't fix a conscience by force.

00:14:11.539 --> 00:14:12.541
You teach them scripture.

00:14:13.061 --> 00:14:17.588
You patiently explain the theology of the new covenant, but you do it over time.

00:14:18.068 --> 00:14:21.533
You let their conscience catch up to their theology at its own speed.

00:14:21.673 --> 00:14:22.474
You disciple them.

00:14:22.694 --> 00:14:23.656
You don't bulldoze them.

00:14:23.796 --> 00:14:24.236
Exactly.

00:14:24.957 --> 00:14:28.402
Pushing someone to violate their conscience before they are ready,

00:14:28.514 --> 00:14:29.195
is dangerous.

00:14:29.495 --> 00:14:33.459
And the third habit, defer quickly, discuss slowly.

00:14:34.019 --> 00:14:35.741
This is the golden rule for conflict.

00:14:35.941 --> 00:14:41.987
In the immediate moment, at the table, at the party, if you sense tension, defer.

00:14:42.207 --> 00:14:42.787
Just give it up.

00:14:43.068 --> 00:14:45.770
Give it up, put the glass down, change the subject.

00:14:46.070 --> 00:14:47.932
Prioritize the relationship in that second.

00:14:48.373 --> 00:14:50.915
Don't have the big theological debate when emotions are high.

00:14:51.115 --> 00:14:54.839
But discuss slowly means we don't just ignore it forever.

00:14:54.979 --> 00:14:55.159
Right.

00:14:55.659 --> 00:14:58.482
Later, over coffee, when everyone is calm,

00:14:58.754 --> 00:14:59.455
You open the Bible.

00:14:59.875 --> 00:15:00.576
You talk about it.

00:15:00.936 --> 00:15:05.561
You seek unity and understanding, but you separate the moment from the process.

00:15:05.902 --> 00:15:07.063
That is so helpful.

00:15:07.203 --> 00:15:10.066
It stops freedom from becoming a weapon in the moment.

00:15:10.226 --> 00:15:13.270
And it keeps the church from fracturing over things that aren't the gospel.

00:15:13.450 --> 00:15:17.714
We have covered a lot of ground today, from blood sausage to modern polarization.

00:15:18.115 --> 00:15:24.722
But as we wrap up, it really seems like Romans 14.1315 is giving us a picture of what a mature community looks like.

00:15:24.902 --> 00:15:25.162
It is.

00:15:25.263 --> 00:15:28.466
It's a community where we belong to the Lord so we don't judge each other.

00:15:28.578 --> 00:15:30.821
And we belong to each other, so we don't hinder each other.

00:15:31.061 --> 00:15:33.744
It sounds restrictive at first, you know, giving up my rights.

00:15:34.405 --> 00:15:35.286
But is it really?

00:15:35.306 --> 00:15:36.428
I don't think so.

00:15:36.928 --> 00:15:38.190
I think it's the ultimate freedom.

00:15:38.510 --> 00:15:40.472
It is the freedom to be like Jesus.

00:15:40.833 --> 00:15:44.798
Jesus had all the rights in the universe, and he laid them down to serve us.

00:15:45.799 --> 00:15:47.942
When we do that for each other, we aren't losing.

00:15:48.222 --> 00:15:49.584
We are looking like our king.

00:15:49.904 --> 00:15:51.246
That is the aha moment.

00:15:51.666 --> 00:15:53.769
True freedom isn't doing whatever I want.

00:15:53.849 --> 00:15:57.273
It's being free enough to love you more than I love my preferences.

00:15:57.413 --> 00:15:58.194
Amen to that.

00:15:58.338 --> 00:16:01.861
So here is the provocative thought we wanna leave you with today.

00:16:02.282 --> 00:16:05.665
We've talked about food and drink, but I mean, this applies to everything.

00:16:06.146 --> 00:16:14.834
Take a look at your life this week, in your interactions online, at work, at church, ask yourself this, are you using your freedom to prove a point?

00:16:15.975 --> 00:16:18.378
Or are you using it to protect the people Christ died for?

00:16:18.498 --> 00:16:21.060
Because at the end of the day, you can be right, or you can be loving.

00:16:21.521 --> 00:16:24.424
And the kingdom of God, love is the final metric.

00:16:24.444 --> 00:16:25.885
Thanks for joining us on this deep dive.

00:16:25.905 --> 00:16:26.866
We'll catch you next time.
